  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\nCurrently, all model filtering/sorting done in status-desktop is imperative, which means javascript for loops in qml code, example:\r\n```qml\r\nfunction orderNamesModel() {\r\n    if(root.orderByReadonly) {\r\n        for(var i = 0; i < namesModel.count; i++) {\r\n            var entry = namesModel.get(i)\r\n            if(entry.isReadonly) {\r\n                namesModel.move(i, 0, 1)\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\nThis approach is a maintenance burden. It's bugprone and produces boilerplate code. It usually leads to some tricky bugs related to source model synchronization issues:\r\n- when the source model is changed (item added, removed, moved) it will not be reflected in the manually built proxy model\r\n- when the property of the model item changes in the source model it will not be reflected in the manually built proxy model\r\n\r\nThe above is usually \"fixed\" by rebuilding the proxy model on every occasion, which eventually may harm the performance as well.\r\n\r\n### Acceptance criteria\r\n- [x] #6510\r\n- [x] #6512\r\n- [x] #6511",
